body: Please share a simple version of your model for us to debug.

Hello I am trying to convert[ this model ](https://github.com/xulabs/aitom/blob/master/aitom/align/deep/gum/Gum-Net.py)using onnx, it has multiple custom layers.

I am getting the same error as the OP. Can you please tell me how can I implement custom layers in keras onnx converter?

Hello, here is a simple example which demonstrates the problem:

```
import keras

import sys
sys.path.insert(0, "./ssd_keras")  #path to https://github.com/pierluigiferrari/ssd_keras

from keras_layers.keras_layer_DecodeDetections import DecodeDetections

import onnxmltools

output_onnx_model = 'model.onnx'

keras_model = keras.Sequential()
keras_model.add(DecodeDetections(img_height=512, img_width=512))
keras_model.build(input_shape=(None, 24564, 98))


onnx_model = onnxmltools.convert_keras(keras_model, target_opset=12)

onnxmltools.utils.save_model(onnx_model, output_onnx_model)
```

To run it you will have to clone https://github.com/pierluigiferrari/ssd_keras
You should use tf2onnx to convert your model. That's now the converter for all tensorflow / keras models.
I am now working on something completely different (it has been a year since the issue was opened), so I am not going to try the tf2onnx now. From my perspective we can close this.
